sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant KServe as KServe Router
    participant OpenAI as OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant TGIS as TGIS gRPC Adapter<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant Engine as vLLM Engine<br/>(PagedAttention)
    participant Worker as GPU Worker
    participant GPU as AMD ROCm GPU<br/>(MI100/MI200/MI300)
    participant Ray as Ray Head<br/>6379/TCP
    participant RayWorker as Ray Workers<br/>Dynamic Ports
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,GPU: Flow 1: OpenAI-Compatible Inference Request

    Client->>OpenAI: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP, Optional TLS<br/>Auth: Optional Bearer Token
    OpenAI->>OpenAI: AuthenticationMiddleware<br/>validates VLLM_API_KEY
    OpenAI->>Engine: Internal: inference request
    Engine->>Worker: Spawn/fork GPU worker
    Worker->>GPU: HIP/ROCm kernel execution<br/>Flash Attention + PagedAttention
    GPU-->>Worker: Inference result
    Worker-->>Engine: Generated tokens
    Engine-->>OpenAI: Completion response
    OpenAI-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>(streaming SSE or batch)

    Note over KServe,GPU: Flow 2: TGIS gRPC Inference Request

    KServe->>TGIS: gRPC GenerationRequest<br/>8033/TCP plaintext
    TGIS->>Engine: Internal: inference request
    Engine->>Worker: Spawn GPU worker
    Worker->>GPU: HIP/ROCm kernel execution
    GPU-->>Worker: Inference result
    Worker-->>Engine: Generated tokens
    Engine-->>TGIS: Generation result
    TGIS-->>KServe: gRPC GenerationResponse

    Note over Engine,RayWorker: Flow 3: Distributed Multi-GPU Inference

    Engine->>Ray: Connect to Ray cluster<br/>6379/TCP Ray Protocol
    Ray->>RayWorker: Distribute to workers<br/>Dynamic ports, Ray Protocol
    RayWorker->>GPU: Parallel GPU execution<br/>RCCL (ROCm NCCL)
    GPU-->>RayWorker: Partial results
    RayWorker-->>Ray: Gather results
    Ray-->>Engine: Aggregated output

    Note over Engine,S3: Model Loading (startup)

    Engine->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM / S3 credentials
    S3-->>Engine: Model weights & tokenizer
